title: Bob Katter Unleashes On Migration As Parliament Debates Hate Speech Laws | 10 News+
description: Independent MP Bob Katter has unleashed on migration, singling out Muslims from the Middle East and North Africa as people he wants to bar from Australia. title: Jewish Teenagers Targeted With Antisemitic Abuse In Melbourne | 10 News
description: Jewish teenagers have had to run for their lives after two suspects hurled antisemitic abuse from a ute in Melbourne. The five schoolboys were forced to hide as they were stalked and intimidated.

title: Trump Threatens Norwegian Prime Minister After Not Winning Nobel Peace Prize | 10 News
description: Donald Trump has told Norway's Prime Minister he "no longer feels an obligation to think purely of peace" — because he didn't get the Nobel Peace Prize. title: Trump Rants About ICE Raids And 'Book Of Accomplishments' | 10 News
description: US President Donald Trump has brought a ‘book of accomplishments’ to the White House press gallery to defend his ‘achievements’ on the first anniversary of his second term in office.  During an address to reporters, he called ICE agents ‘patriots’ and protesters ‘paid agitators’, accused Norway of ‘controlling’ the Nobel Prize, and said the public will ‘find out’ just how far he is willing to go to acquire Greenland.  The President also took aim at the United Nations and NATO. Trump said his Board of Peace might replace the UN, as the UN is ‘unhelpful’. He also said he has done more for NATO than ‘any other person alive or dead’, but doesn’t trust it would return the favour. title: Trump Flips On Renee Good After Learning Her Dad Was A Fan | 10 News
description: US President Donald Trump has called the fatal shooting of Renee Good a 'tragedy' after learning her parents were fans of his administration.  Renee Good, a 37-year-old American citizen, was shot dead by a federal immigration agent on January 7, 2026. The President and Federal law enforcement officials have previously defended the shooting, saying the agent acted in self-defense - a claim which has been vehemently contested by eyewitnesses and video evidence.  Trump also conceded that ICE is sometimes going to be "too rough" with somebody, and sometimes mistakes "can happen".  The comments happened during Trump's speech to the White House press gallery about his ‘book of accomplishments’, listing his ‘achievements’ so far in his second term of office. title: Macron Rebukes Trump Over Greenland As Carney Urges Middle Powers To Unite | 10 News
description: French President Emmanuel Macron has blasted Donald Trump’s Greenland ambitions, warning Europe won’t bow to “new imperialism” and urging the EU to consider tough trade sanctions.  Addressing the World Economic Forum in Davos, Macron urged the bloc to toughen its stance and defend rule-of-law against political “bullies”, pointing to the EU’s so-called anti-coercion “trade bazooka”.  Canada’s Prime Minister Mark Carney backed Europe, arguing middle powers must unite to resist coercion from major states.  Carney cautioned that if like-minded countries aren’t “at the table”, they risk ending up “on the menu”.
